create a static memeber hold only one instance of singleton
create a private construcot to avoid external instntiation
use a metohd to create singleton instance

	public class Singleton {
	    // Static member holds only one instance of Singleton
	    private static Singleton instance;
	
	    // Private constructor avoids external instantiation
	    private Singleton() {
	        // Initialization code here
	    }
	
	    // Static factory method to get the singleton instance
	    public static Singleton getInstance() {
	        if (instance == null) {
	            instance = new Singleton();
	        }
	        return instance;
	    }
	}
This pattern helps in resource management like caching, logging, or database connection
 pooling by centralizing the instance control and providing global access efficiently.